  "prompt": "Why won't IFTTT link to my tumblr account?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why IFTTT isn't linking to your Tumblr account. Here are some common issues and troubleshooting steps to help resolve the problem:\n\n1. **Tumblr API Issues**: Tumblr's API might be experiencing downtime or restrictions. Try checking Tumblr's status or waiting a few hours before trying again.\n\n2. **IFTTT Service Outage**: IFTTT might be experiencing issues on their end. Check IFTTT's status page or social media for updates.\n\n3. **Account Permissions**: Ensure that you\u2019ve granted IFTTT the necessary permissions to access your Tumblr account. During the linking process, you\u2019ll need to authorize IFTTT to connect to Tumblr.\n\n4. **Browser Issues**: If you\u2019re using a browser, clear your cache and cookies or try an incognito/private window. Alternatively, use the IFTTT mobile app.\n\n5. **Incorrect Credentials**: Double-check that you\u2019re entering the correct Tumblr username and password.\n\n6. **Security Settings**: Tumblr might block third-party apps like IFTTT if your account has strict security settings. Check Tumblr\u2019s security or privacy settings and ensure third-party app access is allowed.\n\n7. **App Version**: If you\u2019re using the IFTTT mobile app, ensure it\u2019s updated to the latest version.\n\n8. **Re-Linking the Account**:\n   - Go to IFTTT and disconnect Tumblr from your account.\n   - Reconnect Tumblr and follow the steps to authorize IFTTT again.\n\n9. **Tumblr Terms of Service**: Tumblr may have updated its terms of service or API policies, which could limit integration with third-party apps like IFTTT.\n\n10. **Account Suspension**: If your Tumblr account is suspended or restricted, IFTTT won\u2019t be able to connect to it. Check your Tumblr account status.\n\nIf none of these steps work, consider reaching out to:\n\n- **IFTTT Support**: Contact IFTTT\u2019s support team for assistance.\n- **Tumblr Support**: Check with Tumblr to ensure there are no issues on their end.\n\nLet me know if you need further help!",
